<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: im not expert.. then experts must ask it but..]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1060&amp;p=9036#p9036"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">lord_Chile wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />and do you know a compiler that supports make .sav 8kb sram??<br /></div><br />lord_Chile, you don't do that with the compiler/assembler. You don't "make" the .sav file. When your NES program/game uses the memory at $6000-$7FFF you're using extra ram, and the emulator will save that to a file, to simulate the way a batery would keep the data in a real cart.<br /><br />If you want to have save ram, just use the ram at $6000-$7FFF.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Feb 03, 2006 8:43 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
